<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FE5FE6B48F75146FACFF8E2" pageId="427" pageNumber="428" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="007606418FE5FE6B48F75146FACFF8E2" blockId="427.[151,1436,1606,1955]" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE5FE6B48F75146FEE4F973" bold="true" box="[199,321,1642,1667]" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE5FE6B497A5147FE3BF973" box="[330,414,1643,1667]" italics="true" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE5FE6B49805146FDF6F972" box="[432,595,1642,1666]" captionStart="PLATE 134" captionStartId="428.[151,234,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[281,1301,185,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-41@428.[262,1325,169,1969]" captionTargetPageId="428" captionText="PLATE 134. Esagonatopus perdebilis, female from USA, Arizona, Nogales. Length 3.0 mm (from Olmi 1984). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278846/files/figure.png" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Plate 134A, B</figureCitation>
): apterous (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE5FE6B4AEE5146FC25F972" box="[734,896,1642,1666]" captionStart="PLATE 134" captionStartId="428.[151,234,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[281,1301,185,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-41@428.[262,1325,169,1969]" captionTargetPageId="428" captionText="PLATE 134. Esagonatopus perdebilis, female from USA, Arizona, Nogales. Length 3.0 mm (from Olmi 1984). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278846/files/figure.png" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Plate 134A, B</figureCitation>
); palpal formula 6/2; antenna without rhinaria; pronotum crossed by strong transverse impression (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE5FE6B4AD051A2FCF8F956" box="[736,861,1678,1702]" captionStart="PLATE 134" captionStartId="428.[151,234,1964,1987]" captionTargetBox="[281,1301,185,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-41@428.[262,1325,169,1969]" captionTargetPageId="428" captionText="PLATE 134. Esagonatopus perdebilis, female from USA, Arizona, Nogales. Length 3.0 mm (from Olmi 1984). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278846/files/figure.png" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Plate 134B</figureCitation>
); enlarged claw with distal apex pointed, with one small subapical tooth, without lamellae, with bristles or peg-like hairs (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE5FE6B4B88519EFB93F93A" box="[952,1078,1714,1738]" captionStart="PLATE 136" captionStartId="430.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,273,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-52@430.[198,1388,253,1844]" captionTargetPageId="430" captionText="PLATE 136. Esagonatopus sinensis sp. nov., holotype. A. Chela. B. Mesosoma, lateral view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.10 mm for A, 0.40 mm for B and C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278850/files/figure.png" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Plate 136A</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/0/1. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE5FE6B4D2A519FFAF6F93B" box="[1306,1363,1715,1739]" italics="true" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE5FE6B4D54519EFF53F91E" captionStart="PLATE 135" captionStartId="429.[151,234,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[283,1309,221,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-38@429.[258,1329,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="429" captionText="PLATE 135. Esagonatopus niger, male from USA, Kentucky, Lexington. Length 2.0 mm (from Olmi 1984). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278848/files/figure.png" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Plate 135A, B</figureCitation>
): fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE5FE6B499B51FAFDEDF91E" box="[427,584,1750,1774]" captionStart="PLATE 135" captionStartId="429.[151,234,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[283,1309,221,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-38@429.[258,1329,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="429" captionText="PLATE 135. Esagonatopus niger, male from USA, Kentucky, Lexington. Length 2.0 mm (from Olmi 1984). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278848/files/figure.png" pageId="427" pageNumber="428">Plate 135A, B</figureCitation>
); occipital carina absent or incomplete; in this last case, only present behind and shortly on sides of posterior ocelli; occiput concave; temple present; palpal formula 6/2; tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
